<anmlpepl@whidbey.com>

[It may be that transmission of rabies can occur as a consequence of
butchering of rabid animals and the unwise consumption of raw dog
meat. However in the current outbreak in the province of Catanduanes,
where children during the school vacation period are the predominate
victims, transmission is likely to be through direct contact with
live rabid animals. - Mod.CP]
